<br>
                                                    Strydin- 35th Ranger <br>
                                                    Lore Tactition<br>
                                                    Warders Of Lore <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Looter</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 3:48:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for imput for items in hunt</span><hr size=1> Have one team recover 70 tarnished daggers from the pool at Shadow Haven's entrance.<br>
<br>
Have three of your members search the entire Kithicor forest for an Evergreen Leaf between the hours of 9 PM and 9 AM. <p>-----<br><img . src="http://www.members.aol.com/aquasol/neosig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 3:54:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Items</span><hr size=1> At those levels, mid-level quest items are great. <br>
<br>
Like the icon from the goblin in Runnyeye, for cleric quest armor. In fact, the cleric quest armor has a lot of pieces that would be fun for scavangers... (Some are items that spawn on the ground, like the item in Kith and the item in Guk)<br>
<br>
Or a decaying BP from the lizards in Feerrott. Or other mid-level quest items. <br>
<br>
Etc, etc. <br>
<br>
Lots of those would be fun, and the TLC should hit you. <br>
<br>
<br>
-Krazak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 761<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 4:07:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Items</span><hr size=1> The hard thing is gonna be finding things that someone doesn't already have in the bank, or can't get easily in some non-scavenger-hunt way.<br>
<br>
Are you looking for them to actually kill things and get certain loot, or just looking to make them run around? If all you want is for them to run around, you could have friends/guildmates in certain areas with stuff, and they could give clues to the next place. An example (since that wasn't clear)...<br>
<br>
Everyone starts in Felwithe, for example. They are all told &quot;Seek the first clue in waters blue... Skins of blue will guard it, too&quot;. Although this could refer to someplace in Crushbone (orcs and water) , or someplace near the aqua goblins at the Butcherblock docks, it actually refers to someone waiting on the island in the middle of Dagnor's Cauldron. (Multiple possible solutions make for a bit of difficulty).<br>
<br>
Someone from the guild who is carrying or wearing some obvious item (so they know they found the right guy) gives them a wolf sandwich and their next clue... &quot;We look to the stars&quot; - a reference to one of the several gnomish observatories (pick one, stick your next guy there).<br>
<br>
Make sense?<br>
<br>
We've done these things out here in reality and they were a heck of alot of fun.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Just an idea - ignore if it isn't your cup of tea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Looter</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 4:19:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Items</span><hr size=1> What is the incentive for your guild members?<br>
<br>
While I admire the fact that I'm able to take a leisurely, slow walk around Norrath, I don't want to do it for no reason. Are you offering platinum or some equipment or something for the team that finishes first? <p>-----<br><img . src="http://www.members.aol.com/aquasol/neosig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustrydin9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Strydin9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 5:53:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Items</span><hr size=1> Well the general idea is to get them to use their shared knowledge to collect both looted items and bought (such as any items that can only be bought in certain locations. not costly items.  simple things like oyster sauce)   And yes there is an incentive. The members of the winning team will each get to choose an item from the guild vault or 100p as of now.  We may make it higher.  All of us officers are talking about the prizes more. So just items that will take time and hey if they want to purchase the stuff thats on them.  And we are lookng for items players would not normally hold onto and have on them or in the bank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uiristreedawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iris Treedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/10/02 12:36:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for imput for items in hunt</span><hr size=1> How about a fish unique to a particular zone?<br>
